column5: Took part in the 1st Annual Nestor Falls Muskie Cup this year, it was a blast, well organised , and well times event,, this first year was a bit short or entries , but not in the fun and good fishing,, lots of fish were caught ranging from small muskies to a 50 incher caught on the first day by myself and my partner as we won it hands down,, if you are on Facebook look it up, was a great time and good fun for all involved,, https://fbcdn-sphotos-g-a.akamaihd.n...48752400_n.jpg

from left to right in the picture is, John, emcee and all around good fisherman, Mike Grant, Team Captain of the winning team and excellent muskie fisherman, The Cup, Pete Corkey,, me and Co Captain of the winning team Terry Brennan , owner of C and C (Clark and Crombie Camp , Nestor Falls,) and organizer of event,, Byron Walker Tinker's ( Nestor Falls )and the other organizer of the event,,
happening next weekend, come on up ,
Here's the website for more information and pictures:http://www.nestorfallsmuskycup.com
